ğŸ§  Problem: Reverse an Array

Difficulty: EasyTopic: Arrays

ğŸ“ Problem Statement

Given an array of integers, reverse the array in-place without using extra space.

ğŸ” Example

Input: arr[] = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}  
Output: {5, 4, 3, 2, 1}

Input: arr[] = {10, 20, 30}  
Output: {30, 20, 10}

ğŸš€ Approach

Use two pointers, one at the start (i = 0) and one at the end (n-1).

Swap the elements at these two positions.

Move both pointers towards the center and repeat until they meet.

âœ… Java Solution

public class ReverseArray {
    void reverse(int[] arr) {
        int n = arr.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
            int temp = arr[i];
            arr[i] = arr[n - 1 - i];
            arr[n - 1 - i] = temp;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ReverseArray obj = new ReverseArray();
        int[] arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
        obj.reverse(arr);
        System.out.print("Reversed Array: ");
        for (int num : arr) {
            System.out.print(num + " ");
        }
    }
}

ğŸ§ª Output

Reversed Array: 5 4 3 2 1

